    <note>Huangfu(1) Lu [30676] MS, 287.7375 identifies his sons as first cousins of a different surname of Huang(2) Luzeng [30667] and Huang(2) Shengzeng [30668]. There are two possibilities, which may be resolved by a CHECK of various funerary sources. The Huang(2) brothers were sons of Huangfu(1) Lu's sister, or Huangfu Lu was married to the sister of the two Huang(2) brothers' father. We guess that the former was true in order to establish the kindred connections. MS, 287.7373-7375. Changzhou XZ (1571), 6.11b, 22a, 14.33b.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1492:  passed the juren exam.</note>
